Portuguese and Manchester United footballer, Cristiano Ronaldo, has broken the world record to become the first person to have 400 million followers on the social media platform, Instagram. Ronaldo has 400 million followers, only follows 501 people on the app, with 3242 posts, and an average of 10 million ‘likes’ on his posts. According to reports gathered, the footballer beats reality star, Kylie Jenner who has over 308million followers, with Lionel Messi ranking third with 306million followers.